   "source": [
    ":orphan:\n",
    "\n",
    ".. _molecule:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "raw_mimetype": "text/restructuredtext"
   },
   "source": [
    "# Generate a molecule\n",
    "This section describes the basics of creating molecule objects and their structures."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "metadata": {
    "raw_mimetype": "text/restructuredtext"
   },
   "source": [
    ".. raw:: html\n",
    "\n",
    "   <div class=col-md-9>"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {
    "nbsphinx": "hidden"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "import pymol\n",
    "import xmlrpc.client as xmlrpclib"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {
    "nbsphinx": "hidden"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "os.system(\"pymol -R &\")\n",
    "cmd = xmlrpclib.ServerProxy('http://localhost:9123')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {
    "nbsphinx": "hidden"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from pymol import cmd\n",
    "from IPython.display import Image\n",
    "from PIL             import Image\n",
    "\n",
    "from porems.store import Store"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {
    "nbsphinx": "hidden"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def img_pymol(mol, pic, label=True):\n",
    "    # Save gro file\n",
    "    Store(mol,\"_build\").gro(\"temp.gro\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Load into pymol\n",
    "    cmd.delete(\"all\")\n",
    "    cmd.load(\"_build/temp.gro\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Edit view\n",
    "    cmd.set_color(\"deepBlue\",[0.00, 0.45, 0.70])\n",
    "    cmd.color(\"deepBlue\")\n",
    "    cmd.label(\"all\",\"name\")\n",
    "    cmd.set(\"label_color\",\"white\",\"all\")\n",
    "    cmd.set(\"label_size\",20)\n",
    "    cmd.set(\"label_font_id\",5)\n",
    "    cmd.set(\"specular\",\"off\")\n",
    "    cmd.set(\"surface_quality\",4)\n",
    "    cmd.set(\"sphere_quality\",2)\n",
    "    cmd.set(\"ray_shadows\",\"off\")\n",
    "    cmd.set(\"ray_trace_mode\",5)\n",
    "    cmd.set(\"ray_opaque_background\",0)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Generate image\n",
    "    pic_link = \"/tmp/\"+pic+\".png\"\n",
    "    cmd.png(pic_link,width=400,height=400,dpi=1000,ray=1)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Load image\n",
    "    img = Image.open(pic_link)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Display image\n",
    "    display(img)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Initialize object\n",
    "An empty Molecule object can be easily created by passing no input. Remember to set a name to the molecule, which is also defined in the molecule config file."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from porems.molecule import Molecule\n",
    "\n",
    "mol = Molecule()\n",
    "mol.set_name(\"benzene\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Create structure\n",
    "It is possible to create the structures by passing a coordinate."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "mol.add(\"C\", [0, 0, 0])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<PIL.PngImagePlugin.PngImageFile image mode=RGBA size=400x400 at 0x10CF34048>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "img_pymol(mol, \"01\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Position dependent placing\n",
    "If the molecule has at least one atom, other atoms can be added depending on that position by passing the reference atom index a distance and an angle. In this case the angle depends on the z plane."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "mol.add(\"C\", 0, r=0.1375, theta=60)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<PIL.PngImagePlugin.PngImageFile image mode=RGBA size=400x400 at 0x10CF29C88>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "img_pymol(mol, \"02\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Final molecule\n",
    "Complete the ring structure of the benzene molecule."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "mol.add(\"C\", 1, r=0.1375, theta=120)\n",
    "mol.add(\"C\", 2, r=0.1375, theta=180)\n",
    "mol.add(\"C\", 3, r=0.1375, theta=240)\n",
    "mol.add(\"C\", 4, r=0.1375, theta=300)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<PIL.PngImagePlugin.PngImageFile image mode=RGBA size=400x400 at 0x10CF262B0>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "img_pymol(mol, \"03\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Rotate molecule\n",
    "For viewing purposes the molecule can be rotated. This function might also be needed for specific molecule positioning.\n",
    "At the end of creating a structure consider resetting the point of origin."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "mol.rotate(\"x\", angle=90)\n",
    "mol.zero()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<PIL.PngImagePlugin.PngImageFile image mode=RGBA size=400x400 at 0x10C9857B8>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "img_pymol(mol, \"04\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Save Structure\n",
    "Using the write class, the generated structures can be exported into various formats."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 17,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from porems.store import Store\n",
    "\n",
    "Store(mol).gro()\n",
    "Store(mol).pdb()\n",
    "Store(mol).xyz()"
   ]
  }
 ],
